events.description: The Republic of Pisa is defeated in the Battle of Meloria by the Republic of Genoa, thus losing its naval dominance in the Mediterranean.
events.html: • 1284 – The Republic of Pisa is defeated in the Battle of Meloria by the Republic of Genoa, thus losing its naval dominance in the Mediterranean.[1]

events.description: Bogotá, Colombia, is founded by Gonzalo Jiménez de Quesada.
events.html: • 1538 – Bogotá, Colombia, is founded by Gonzalo Jiménez de Quesada.[2]

events.description: The Treaty of The Hague is signed by Portugal and the Dutch Republic.
events.html: • 1661 – The Treaty of The Hague is signed by Portugal and the Dutch Republic.[3]

events.description: American Revolutionary War: The bloody Battle of Oriskany prevents American relief of the Siege of Fort Stanwix.
events.html: • 1777 – American Revolutionary War: The bloody Battle of Oriskany prevents American relief of the Siege of Fort Stanwix.[4]

events.description: Sixty proof sheets of the Constitution of the United States are delivered to the Constitutional Convention in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.
events.html: • 1787 – Sixty proof sheets of the Constitution of the United States are delivered to the Constitutional Convention in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.

events.description: Francis II, Holy Roman Emperor, declares the moribund empire to be dissolved, although he retains power in the Austrian Empire.
events.html: • 1806 – Francis II, Holy Roman Emperor, declares the moribund empire to be dissolved, although he retains power in the Austrian Empire.[5]

events.description: Norwich University is founded in Vermont as the first private military school in the United States.
events.html: • 1819 – Norwich University is founded in Vermont as the first private military school in the United States.

events.description: Peruvian War of Independence: Patriot forces led by Simón Bolívar defeat the Spanish Royalist army in the Battle of Junín.
events.html: • 1824 – Peruvian War of Independence: Patriot forces led by Simón Bolívar defeat the Spanish Royalist army in the Battle of Junín.[6]

events.description: The Bolivian Declaration of Independence is proclaimed.
events.html: • 1825 – The Bolivian Declaration of Independence is proclaimed.

events.description: Britain imposes the Lagos Treaty of Cession to suppress slavery in what is now Nigeria.
events.html: • 1861 – Britain imposes the Lagos Treaty of Cession to suppress slavery in what is now Nigeria.

events.description: American Civil War: The Confederate ironclad CSS Arkansas is scuttled on the Mississippi River after suffering catastrophic engine failure near Baton Rouge, Louisiana.
events.html: • 1862 – American Civil War: The Confederate ironclad CSS Arkansas is scuttled on the Mississippi River after suffering catastrophic engine failure near Baton Rouge, Louisiana.

events.description: Franco-Prussian War: The Battle of Spicheren is fought, resulting in a German victory.
events.html: • 1870 – Franco-Prussian War: The Battle of Spicheren is fought, resulting in a German victory.

events.description: Franco-Prussian War: The Battle of Wörth results in a decisive German victory.
events.html: • 1870 – Franco-Prussian War: The Battle of Wörth results in a decisive German victory.

events.description: At Auburn Prison in New York, murderer William Kemmler becomes the first person to be executed by electric chair.
events.html: • 1890 – At Auburn Prison in New York, murderer William Kemmler becomes the first person to be executed by electric chair.

events.description: Kiowa land in Oklahoma is opened for white settlement, effectively dissolving the contiguous reservation.
events.html: • 1901 – Kiowa land in Oklahoma is opened for white settlement, effectively dissolving the contiguous reservation.

events.description: World War I: U-boat campaign: Two days after the United Kingdom had declared war on Germany over the German invasion of Belgium, ten German U-boats leave their base in Heligoland to attack Royal Navy warships in the North Sea.
events.html: • 1914 – World War I: U-boat campaign: Two days after the United Kingdom had declared war on Germany over the German invasion of Belgium, ten German U-boats leave their base in Heligoland to attack Royal Navy warships in the North Sea.

events.description: World War I: Serbia declares war on Germany; Austria declares war on Russia.
events.html: • 1914 – World War I: Serbia declares war on Germany; Austria declares war on Russia.

events.description: World War I: Battle of Sari Bair: The Allies mount a diversionary attack timed to coincide with a major Allied landing of reinforcements at Suvla Bay.
events.html: • 1915 – World War I: Battle of Sari Bair: The Allies mount a diversionary attack timed to coincide with a major Allied landing of reinforcements at Suvla Bay.

events.description: World War I: Battle of Mărășești between the Romanian and German armies begins.
events.html: • 1917 – World War I: Battle of Mărășești between the Romanian and German armies begins.

events.description: Gertrude Ederle becomes the first woman to swim across the English Channel.
events.html: • 1926 – Gertrude Ederle becomes the first woman to swim across the English Channel.

events.description: First public screening using the Vitaphone process
events.html: • 1926 – First public screening using the Vitaphone process[7]

events.description: Estonia is annexed by the Soviet Union.
events.html: • 1940 – Estonia is annexed by the Soviet Union.[8]

events.description: Queen Wilhelmina of the Netherlands becomes the first reigning queen to address a joint session of the United States Congress.
events.html: • 1942 – Queen Wilhelmina of the Netherlands becomes the first reigning queen to address a joint session of the United States Congress.

events.description: The Warsaw Uprising occurs on August 1. It is brutally suppressed and all able-bodied men in Kraków are detained afterwards to prevent a similar uprising, the Kraków Uprising, that was planned but never carried out.
events.html: • 1944 – The Warsaw Uprising occurs on August 1. It is brutally suppressed and all able-bodied men in Kraków are detained afterwards to prevent a similar uprising, the Kraków Uprising, that was planned but never carried out.

events.description: World War II: Hiroshima, Japan is devastated when the atomic bomb "Little Boy" is dropped by the United States B-29 Enola Gay. Around 70,000 people are killed instantly, and some tens of thousands die in subsequent years from burns and radiation poisoning.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Hiroshima, Japan is devastated when the atomic bomb "Little Boy" is dropped by the United States B-29 Enola Gay. Around 70,000 people are killed instantly, and some tens of thousands die in subsequent years from burns and radiation poisoning.

entities.name: Atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki

events.description: After going bankrupt in 1955, the American broadcaster DuMont Television Network makes its final broadcast, a boxing match from St. Nicholas Arena in New York in the Boxing from St. Nicholas Arena series.
events.html: • 1956 – After going bankrupt in 1955, the American broadcaster DuMont Television Network makes its final broadcast, a boxing match from St. Nicholas Arena in New York in the Boxing from St. Nicholas Arena series.

events.description: Law of Permanent Defense of Democracy, outlawing the Communist Party of Chile and banning 26,650 persons from the electoral lists, is repealed in Chile.
events.html: • 1958 – Law of Permanent Defense of Democracy, outlawing the Communist Party of Chile and banning 26,650 persons from the electoral lists,[9] is repealed in Chile.[10]

entities.name: Law of Permanent Defense of Democracy

events.description: Cuban Revolution: Cuba nationalizes American and foreign-owned property in the nation.
events.html: • 1960 – Cuban Revolution: Cuba nationalizes American and foreign-owned property in the nation.

events.description: Jamaica becomes independent from the United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1962 – Jamaica becomes independent from the United Kingdom.[11]

events.description: US President Lyndon B. Johnson signs the Voting Rights Act of 1965 into law.
events.html: • 1965 – US President Lyndon B. Johnson signs the Voting Rights Act of 1965 into law.

events.description: A low-pressure system that redeveloped off the New South Wales coast dumps a record 328 millimeters (13 inches) of rain in a day on Sydney, New South Wales, Australia.
events.html: • 1986 – A low-pressure system that redeveloped off the New South Wales coast dumps a record 328 millimeters (13 inches) of rain in a day on Sydney, New South Wales, Australia.

events.description: Gulf War: The United Nations Security Council orders a global trade embargo against Iraq in response to Iraq's invasion of Kuwait.
events.html: • 1990 – Gulf War: The United Nations Security Council orders a global trade embargo against Iraq in response to Iraq's invasion of Kuwait.

events.description: Tim Berners-Lee releases files describing his idea for the World Wide Web. WWW makes its first appearance as a publicly available service on the Internet.
events.html: • 1991 – Tim Berners-Lee releases files describing his idea for the World Wide Web. WWW makes its first appearance as a publicly available service on the Internet.

events.description: Takako Doi, chair of the Social Democratic Party, becomes Japan's first female speaker of the House of Representatives.
events.html: • 1991 – Takako Doi, chair of the Social Democratic Party, becomes Japan's first female speaker of the House of Representatives.

events.description: NASA announces that the ALH 84001 meteorite, thought to originate from Mars, contains evidence of primitive life-forms.
events.html: • 1996 – NASA announces that the ALH 84001 meteorite, thought to originate from Mars, contains evidence of primitive life-forms.

events.description: Korean Air Flight 801 crashed at Nimitz Hill, Guam, killing 229 of the 254 people on board.
events.html: • 1997 – Korean Air Flight 801 crashed at Nimitz Hill, Guam, killing 229 of the 254 people on board.[12]

events.description: Erwadi fire incident: Twenty-eight mentally ill persons tied to a chain are burnt to death at a faith based institution at Erwadi, Tamil Nadu.
events.html: • 2001 – Erwadi fire incident: Twenty-eight mentally ill persons tied to a chain are burnt to death at a faith based institution at Erwadi, Tamil Nadu.[13]

events.description: A military junta led by Mohamed Ould Abdel Aziz stages a coup d'état in Mauritania, overthrowing president Sidi Ould Cheikh Abdallahi.
events.html: • 2008 – A military junta led by Mohamed Ould Abdel Aziz stages a coup d'état in Mauritania, overthrowing president Sidi Ould Cheikh Abdallahi.

events.description: Flash floods across a large part of Jammu and Kashmir, India, damages 71 towns and kills at least 255 people.
events.html: • 2010 – Flash floods across a large part of Jammu and Kashmir, India, damages 71 towns and kills at least 255 people.

events.description: War in Afghanistan: A United States military helicopter is shot down, killing 30 American special forces members and a working dog, seven Afghan soldiers, and one Afghan civilian. It was the deadliest single event for the United States in the War in Afghanistan.
events.html: • 2011 – War in Afghanistan: A United States military helicopter is shot down, killing 30 American special forces members and a working dog, seven Afghan soldiers, and one Afghan civilian. It was the deadliest single event for the United States in the War in Afghanistan.

events.description: NASA's Curiosity rover lands on the surface of Mars.
events.html: • 2012 – NASA's Curiosity rover lands on the surface of Mars.[14]

events.html: • 2015 – A suicide bomb attack kills at least 15 people at a mosque in the Saudi city of Abha.[15]
